Inspired by https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/pull/2036 — backported
to aerospace v0.19.2-Beta (commit 36fde5991eb92cbd422c2ce26bd521dfaec704aa).

PR 2036's main branch base needs Swift 6.2, which only ships in Xcode 17+;
v0.19.2-Beta uses swift-tools-version 6.0 + .swift-version 6.1.2, matching
Xcode 16.4's bundled toolchain. So we backport just the 10-line detector.

Treats Emacs child frames (corfu / eldoc-box / posframe completion popups)
as non-windows so AeroSpace no longer steals focus when they close
(see https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/776).

Matches both Emacs.app (bundle id "org.gnu.Emacs") AND nix-darwin's
CLI-launched emacs daemon, which reports a nil bundle id but axApp AXTitle
"emacs". Uses button-absence as the discriminator (verified empirically
that emacs child frames have no close/min/zoom/fullscreen buttons,
AXMain == false, AXFocused == false; AXSubrole is AXFloatingWindow but we
don't gate on it for robustness across emacs/macOS versions).

--- a/Sources/AppBundle/util/AxUiElementMockEx.swift
+++ b/Sources/AppBundle/util/AxUiElementMockEx.swift
@@ -90,6 +90,21 @@
             return false
         }
 
+        // Emacs child frames (corfu / eldoc-box / posframe popups) are
+        // transient UI elements that should not be managed as windows.
+        let isEmacsApp = appBundleId == "org.gnu.Emacs"
+            || (appBundleId == nil && (axApp.get(Ax.titleAttr) ?? "").lowercased() == "emacs")
+        if isEmacsApp &&
+            get(Ax.closeButtonAttr) == nil &&
+            get(Ax.minimizeButtonAttr) == nil &&
+            get(Ax.zoomButtonAttr) == nil &&
+            get(Ax.fullscreenButtonAttr) == nil &&
+            get(Ax.isMainAttr) != true &&
+            get(Ax.isFocused) != true
+        {
+            return false
+        }
+
         if appBundleId?.isFirefoxId() != true {
             return isWindowHeuristicOld(axApp: axApp, appBundleId: appBundleId)
         }
